C++ Type SQLite Type Binding Method Extraction Method <code>std::string</code> TEXT <code>bind_text()</code> <code>extract_text_ptr()</code> <code>const char*</code> TEXT <code>bind_text()</code> N/A (output only as std::string) <code>std::string_view</code> TEXT <code>bind_text()</code> N/A (output only as std::string) <p>Notes: - Any type convertible to <code>std::string_view</code> can be used for binding - Extraction always returns <code>std::string</code> (owns the data) - Optimized string extraction using <code>sqlite3_column_bytes()</code> (avoids strlen)</p> <p>Usage: <pre><code>struct Document {
    [[=storm::FieldAttr::primary]] int id;
    std::string title;
    std::string content;
};

// All these work for binding:
Document doc1{0, "Title", "Content"};
Document doc2{0, std::string("Title"), std::string("Content")};
std::string_view title_view = "Title";
Document doc3{0, std::string(title_view), "Content"};
</code></pre></p>

C++ Type SQLite Type Binding Method Extraction Method <code>std::optional&lt;T&gt;</code> NULL / T's type <code>bind_null()</code> / recursive <code>is_null()</code> check <p>Supported optional types: - <code>std::optional&lt;int&gt;</code> - <code>std::optional&lt;int64_t&gt;</code> - <code>std::optional&lt;double&gt;</code> - <code>std::optional&lt;float&gt;</code> - <code>std::optional&lt;bool&gt;</code> - <code>std::optional&lt;std::string&gt;</code> - <code>std::optional&lt;std::vector&lt;uint8_t&gt;&gt;</code></p> <p>Behavior: - <code>std::nullopt</code> → SQLite NULL - Value present → Recursively binds the contained value</p> <p>Usage: <pre><code>struct Contact {
    [[=storm::FieldAttr::primary]] int id;
    std::string name;
    std::optional&lt;std::string&gt; email;     // Can be NULL
    std::optional&lt;int&gt; age;               // Can be NULL
    std::optional&lt;bool&gt; is_verified;      // Can be NULL
};

// Examples
Contact c1{1, "Alice", "alice@example.com", 25, true};      // All fields set
Contact c2{2, "Bob", std::nullopt, std::nullopt, std::nullopt}; // NULLs
Contact c3{3, "Charlie", "charlie@example.com", std::nullopt, false}; // Mixed
</code></pre></p>

